item.title: Quantifying Decentralization
item.excerpt: By Balaji S. Srinivasan and Leland Lee The primary advantage of Bitcoin and Ethereum over their legacy alternatives is widely understood to be decentralization. However, despite the widely acknowledged importance of this property, most discussion on the topic lacks quantification.

images.caption: The Lorenz curve is shown in red above. As the cumulative distribution diverges from a straight line, the Gini coefficient
The Lorenz Curve and the Gini Coefficient.

We will use these six subsystems to illustrate how to measure the decentralization of Bitcoin or Ethereum. Please note: you may decide to use different subsystems based on which ones you consider essential to decentralization of the system as a whole.
The Nakamoto coefficient represents the minimum number of entities to compromise a given subsystem. The minimum Nakamoto coefficient is the minimum of the Nakamoto coefficients over all subsystems.
